===Etymology===
Since 16th century; a {{bor|en|fro|epilepsie|nocap=1}}, from {{der|en|la|epilēpsia}}, from {{der|en|grc|ἐπιληψία}}, from {{m|grc|ἐπιλαμβάνω|t=I seize}}, from {{m|grc|ἐπί|t=upon}} + {{m|grc|λαμβάνω|t=I take}}.

===Pronunciation===
* {{IPA|/ˈɛpɪlɛpsi/|lang=en}}
* {{hyphenation|ep|i|lep|sy|lang=en}}

===Noun===
{{en-noun|~|epilepsies}}

# {{lb|en|pathology}} A medical [[condition]] in which the sufferer experiences [[seizure]]s (or [[convulsion]]s) and [[blackout]]s.
#* {{w|Jeremy Taylor}}
#*: '''Epilepsies''', or fallings and reelings, and beastly vomitings. The least of these, even when the tongue begins to be untied, is a degree of drunkenness.

